    "This particular case is a direct orientation of an AluY, which is the Alu subfamily that is most predisposed to brain recombination and, thus, leads to mosaic deletions 58.",
    "We then performed a blast search of the insertion sequence reported by Sniffles2 (and Sanger sequencing, 100% identity) and found that it belongs to an AluYa5.",
    "Across this sample, we could identify 25 other regions that had similar alleles of Alu insertions that lead to mosaic deletions, both identified with Sniffles.",
    "When expanding our search to other sizes of insertions, we identified a total of 206 regions where insertions might lead to an instability of the region, causing a mosaic deletion in the proximity.",
    "This again highlights the ability of Sniffles2 to recover potential interesting alleles genome wide and at scale."
  ],
